ABOUT 40 pupils from a high school in Richards Bay, KZN, have been rushed to hospital after a suspected gas leak around the area. According to Shawn Herbst of Netcare 911, many pupils were affected. “Multiple children have been transported to hospital. Many of them have been vomiting, feeling dizzy and collapsing. A full head count will be done as soon as things have calmed down.” Herbst said residents reported a smell of gas on Saturday night, 5 February. Umhlathuze Municipality spokesman Mdu Ncalane said they were investigating the incident. “We are attending to it together with our fire and rescue and air quality management teams to ascertain what the cause is,” said Ncalane. KZN education spokesman Kwazi Mthethwa the suspected gas leak has affected pupils in Richards Bay Hoerskool. “Our district director is at the school to gather more information and for intervention. Affected pupils have been sent to the nearest hospital for treatment. More details will be made available as soon as possible,” said Mthethwa.